{"title_page": "House of Flanders", "text_new": "{{Original research|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox royal house\n|surname          = House of Flanders\n|type             = <!-- Royal house, noble house, etc. -->\n|native_name      = \n|native_name_lang = \n|other_name       = \n|coat of arms     = Blason Nord-Pas-De-Calais.svg\n|image_size       = 140px\n|alt              = \n|caption          = Arms of the County of Flanders\n|country          = {{flagcountry|Kingdom of France}}<br>{{flagcountry|Holy Roman Empire}}<br>{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Jerusalem}}<br>[[File:Blason Empire Latin de Constantinople.svg|20px]] [[Latin Empire]]\n|estates          = Flanders, Hainaut, Constantinople, Boulogne\n|parent house     = \n|titles           = \n*[[Count of Flanders]]\n*[[Count of Hainaut]]\n*[[Lord of Bouillon]]\n*[[Duke of Lower Lorraine]]\n*[[King of Jerusalem|Defender of the Holy Sepulchre]]\n*[[Count of Edessa]] \n*[[Latin Emperor of Constantinople]]\n*[[Count of Boulogne]]\n*[[King of Jerusalem]]\n*[[Count of Namur]]\n|styles           = \n|founded          = 863\n|founder          = [[Baldwin I, Count of Flanders]]\n|current head     =       \n|deposition       = \n|ethnicity        = Flemish, French\n|cadet branches   = \n*House of Hainaut\n*House of Boulogne\n*House of Mons\n|notes            = \n}}\n\nThe '''House of Flanders'''&mdash;also called ''the Baldwins'' ({{lang-la|Balduini}}, {{lang-fr|Baudouinides}})&mdash;was a medieval royal family founded by [[Baldwin I, Count of Flanders|Baldwin I Iron Arm]], husband of [[Judith of Flanders|Judith]], daughter of [[Charles the Bald]]. They were sovereign counts and styled [[By the Grace of God|by the grace of God]] Count of Flanders.[https://books.google.ca/books?id=v8vwhSwhWogC&pg=PA139&lpg=PA139&dq=gratia+dei+bilbao&source=bl&ots=S-yIgYOh4t&sig=ACfU3U1gm6XyMTHR4rYqr6SsLaXEzcmqwA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiRyLHMktLoAhVGVc0KHb2rDn4Q6AEwAHoECAIQAQ#v=onepage&q=gratia%20dei%20bilbao&f=false] <ref>{{Cite book|last=Jan|first=R\u00e9gine Le|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=v8vwhSwhWogC&dq=gratia+dei+bilbao&q=gratia+dei+#v=snippet&q=gratia%20dei&f=false|title=Famille et pouvoir dans le monde franc (VIIe-Xe si\u00e8cle): essai d'anthropologie sociale|last2=LeJan|first2=R\u00e9gine|date=1995|publisher=Publications de la Sorbonne|isbn=978-2-85944-268-2|language=fr}}</ref>\n\nAt different times various other monarchs such as the French King and Holy Roman Empire attempted to bring Flanders into their rule. However the House of Flanders maintained their sovereignty over Flanders by keeping it as an [[Allod]]. <ref>{{Cite book|last=Longman|first=William|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=YWPVfg7rMoQC&pg=PA124&lpg=PA124&dq=Il+y+avait+la+Flandre+soubs+la+couronne,+relevant+du+roi+de+France+;+la+Flandre+soubs+l'empire,+relevant+de+l'empire;+et+la+Flandre+allodiale,+relevant+directement+du+comte+de+Flandre.%22*+%7C+Voisin,+pp.+49,+50&source=bl&ots=bnSiI8YwVo&sig=ACfU3U0G6GM0SDkSJ51Ac9Nt4N-rCIRgag&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjD8K_Pu_roAhWVGc0KHdo0D20Q6AEwAHoECAgQAQ#v=onepage&q=Allodiale&f=false|title=The History of the Life and Times of Edward III|date=1869|publisher=Longmans & Green|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=124|language=en}}</ref>\n\nFrom 1051, the House of Flanders also reigned over the County of Hainaut, with [[Baldwin VI, Count of Flanders|Baldwin I of Hainaut]]. In  1119, on the death of [[Baldwin VII, Count of Flanders|Baldwin VII]], the House of Flanders had a series of setbacks but in 1191, the House of Flanders recovered the title of Count of Flanders with [[Baldwin VIII, Count of Flanders|Baldwin VIII]] (Baldwin V of Hainaut). The dynasty established the [[Latin Empire of Constantinople]] during the [[Fourth Crusade]]. It also ruled briefly the County of Namur (1188-1212). The House of Flanders was inherited in 1280 by the descendants of [[Margaret II, Countess of Flanders|Margaret II]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Jackson|first=Guida M.|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=x3BzmTdQLioC&pg=PA254&lpg=PA254&dq=count+of+flanders+female+succession&source=bl&ots=U6kWpvpuUg&sig=ACfU3U0rTREk137tCuis4P15IcCzcmEImw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwinvMeZ2_roAhVZZc0KHY7MBbEQ6AEwBHoECAQQAQ#v=onepage&q=count%20of%20flanders%20female%20succession&f=false|title=Women Rulers Throughout the Ages: An Illustrated Guide|last2=Jackson-Laufer|first2=Guida Myrl|last3=Jackson|first3=Lecturer in English Foundations Department Guida M.|date=1999|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-1-57607-091-8|language=en}}</ref>\n\nA cadet branch, the House of Boulogne, ruled over the [[County of Boulogne]]. Members of this house joined the [[First Crusade]], established the [[Kingdom of Jerusalem]], and produced its first kings.\n\n== Genealogy ==\n{{Tree list}}\n*[[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin I, Count of Flanders|Baldwin I Iron Arm]], [[Count of Flanders]] (\u2020 879)\n** {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin II, Count of Flanders|Baldwin II the Bald]], Count of Flanders (\u2020 918)\n***[[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Arnulf I, Count of Flanders|Arnulf I the Great]], Count of Flanders (\u2020 965)\n**** Elftrude, born circa 932, married in 964 to [[File:Blason_ville_fr_Guines_(PDC).png|15px]] Siegfried, Count of Gu\u00eenes (\u2020 965)\n**** Hildegarde (934 \u2020 990), married in 943 to [[File:Counts of Holland Arms.svg|15px]] [[Dirk II, Count of Holland]] (930 \u2020 988)\n**** Egbert (937 \u2020 953)\n**** Liutgarde (938 \u2020 964), married in 950 to Wichmann IV, Count of Hamaland and Ghent.\n**** {{Tree list/final branch}}  [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin III, Count of Flanders|Baldwin III]], Count of Flanders (\u2020 962)\n***** {{Tree list/final branch}}  [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Arnulf II, Count of Flanders|Arnulf II]], Count of Flanders (\u2020 988)\n****** Mathilda (\u2020 995 or before)\n****** {{Tree list/final branch}}  [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin IV, Count of Flanders|