]], Duke of Apulia.\n**********  {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Charles I, Count of Flanders]] (1084 \u2013 1127)\n********* [[Gertrude of Flanders, Duchess of Lorraine|Gertrude]] (1080 - \u2020 1117), married to [[Henry III, Count of Louvain|Henry III]] (\u2020 1095) Count of Louvain and Brussels, then in 1096 to [[Theodoric II, Duke of Lorraine]] (\u2020 1115).\n********* Philip of Loo, whose illegitimate son [[William of Ypres]] was a claimant to the county of Flanders.\n*********  {{Tree list/final branch}} Ogive, abbess of [[Mesen]].\n******* {{Tree list/final branch}}  [[Judith of Flanders, Countess of Northumbria]] (1037 \u2020 1094), married in 1058 to [[Tostig Godwinson]] (\u2020 1066), [[Earl of Northumbria]], then in 1071 to [[Welf I, Duke of Bavaria]] (\u2020 1101)\n*** {{Tree list/final branch}}  [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Adelolf, Count of Boulogne|Adelolf]] (\u2020 933), [[Count of Boulogne]] \n**** {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Arnulf II, Count of Boulogne|Arnulf II]] (\u2020 971), Count of Boulogne\n*****{{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Arnulf III, Count of Boulogne|Arnulf III]] (\u2020 990), Count of Boulogne\n******[[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin II, Count of Boulogne|Baldwin II]] (\u2020 1025), Count of Boulogne \n*******{{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Eustace I, Count of Boulogne|Eustace I]] (v. 995 \u2020 1049), Count of Boulogne\n******** [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Eustace II, Count of Boulogne|Eustace II]] (\u2020 1087), Count of Boulogne\n********* [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Eustace III, Count of Boulogne]] (1056 \u2020 1125)\n********** [[Matilda I, Countess of Boulogne]] (1105 \u2020 1152), married in 1125 to [[Stephen of England]]\n********* [[Godfrey of Bouillon]] (1058 \u2020 1099), [[Duke of Lower Lorraine]], a leader of the [[First Crusade]] and \"Advocate of the Holy Sepulchre\"\n********* {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Armoiries de J\u00e9rusalem.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin I of Jerusalem]] (1065 \u2020 1118), accompanied his brother to the Holy Land, became Count of Edessa and then King of Jerusalem\n******** Godfrey (\u2020 1095), Bishop of Paris\n******** [[Lambert II, Count of Lens]] (\u2020 1054)\n******** {{Tree list/final branch}} Gerberge (\u2020 1049), married [[Frederick, Duke of Lower Lorraine]] (1003 \u2020 1065)\n******{{Tree list/final branch}} Arnulf IV, Count of Ternois\n{{Tree list/end}}\n\n==Arms==\n{{Multiple image\n<!-- Essential parameters -->\n | align             = center\n | direction         = <!-- horizontal (default), vertical -->\n | background color  = <!-- box background -->\n\n<!-- Header -->\n | header_background = \n | header_align      = <!-- center (default), left, right -->\n | header            = Arms of the House of Flanders\n\n<!-- Images -->\n | width             = 140\n<!--image 1-->\n | image1            = Blason Flandre ancien.svg\n | caption1          = Count of Flanders (attributed)\n<!--image 2-->\n | image2            = Blason Nord-Pas-De-Calais.svg\n | caption2          = Count of Flanders\n<!--image 3-->\n | image3            = Blason fr Hainaut ancien.svg\n | caption3          = Count of Hainaut (Ancient)\n<!--image 4-->\n | image4            = Blason Empire Latin de Constantinople.svg\n | caption4          = Latin Emperor of Constantinople\n\n<!-- and so on, to a maximum of 10 images (image10) -->\n\n}}\n\n{{Multiple image\n<!-- Essential parameters -->\n | align             = center\n | direction         = <!-- horizontal (default), vertical -->\n | background color  = <!-- box background -->\n\n<!-- Header -->\n | header_background = \n | header_align      = <!-- center (default), left, right -->\n | header            = Arms of the House of Boulogne\n\n<!-- Images -->\n | width             = 140\n<!--image 1-->\n | image1            = Blason Courtenay.svg\n | caption1          = Count of Boulogne\n<!--image 2-->\n | image2            = Armoiries de J\u00e9rusalem.svg\n | caption2          = King of Jerusalem\n\n<!-- and so on, to a maximum of 10 images (image10) -->\n\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:County Of Flanders}}\n[[Category:Flanders]]\n[[Category:County of Flanders| ]]\n[[Category:Counts of Flanders| ]]\n[[Category:House of Flanders| ]]\n[[Category:Carolingian dynasty|*]]\n", "text_old": "{{Original research|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox royal house\n|surname          = House of Flanders\n|type             = <!-- Royal house, noble house, etc. -->\n|native_name      = \n|native_name_lang = \n|other_name       = \n|coat of arms     = Blason Nord-Pas-De-Calais.svg\n|image_size       = 140px\n|alt              = \n|caption          = Arms of the County of Flanders\n|country          = {{flagcountry|Kingdom of France}}<br>{{flagcountry|Holy Roman Empire}}<br>{{flagcountry|Kingdom of Jerusalem}}<br>[[File:Blason Empire Latin de Constantinople.svg|20px]] [[Latin Empire]]\n|estates          = Flanders, Hainaut, Constantinople, Boulogne\n|parent house     = \n|titles           = \n*[[Count of Flanders]]\n*[[Count of Hainaut]]\n*[[Lord of Bouillon]]\n*[[Duke of Lower Lorraine]]\n*[[King of Jerusalem|Defender of the Holy Sepulchre]]\n*[[Count of Edessa]] \n*[[Latin Emperor of Constantinople]]\n*[[Count of Boulogne]]\n*[[King of Jerusalem]]\n*[[Count of Namur]]\n|styles           = \n|founded          = 863\n|founder          = [[Baldwin I, Count of Flanders]]\n|current head     =       \n|deposition       = \n|ethnicity        = Flemish, French\n|cadet branches   = \n*House of Hainaut\n*House of Boulogne\n*House of Mons\n|notes            = \n}}\n\nThe '''House of Flanders'''&mdash;also called ''the Baldwins'' ({{lang-la|Balduini}}, {{lang-fr|Baudouinides}})&mdash;was a medieval royal family founded by [[Baldwin I, Count of Flanders|Baldwin I Iron Arm]], husband of [[Judith of Flanders|Judith]], daughter of [[Charles the Bald]]. They were sovereign counts and styled [[By the Grace of God|by the grace of God]] Count of Flanders.[https://books.google.ca/books?id=v8vwhSwhWogC&pg=PA139&lpg=PA139&dq=gratia+dei+bilbao&source=bl&ots=S-yIgYOh4t&sig=ACfU3U1gm6XyMTHR4rYqr6SsLaXEzcmqwA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiRyLHMktLoAhVGVc0KHb2rDn4Q6AEwAHoECAIQAQ#v=onepage&q=gratia%20dei%20bilbao&f=false] <ref>{{Cite book|last=Jan|first=R\u00e9gine Le|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=v8vwhSwhWogC&dq=gratia+dei+bilbao&q=gratia+dei+#v=snippet&q=gratia%20dei&f=false|title=Famille et pouvoir dans le monde franc (VIIe-Xe si\u00e8cle): essai d'anthropologie sociale|last2=LeJan|first2=R\u00e9gine|date=1995|publisher=Publications de la Sorbonne|isbn=978-2-85944-268-2|language=fr}}</ref>\n\nAt different times various other monarchs such as the French King and Holy Roman Empire attempted to bring Flanders into thier rule. However the House of Flanders maintained thier sovereignty over Flanders by keeping it as an [[Allod]]. <ref>{{Cite book|last=Longman|first=William|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=YWPVfg7rMoQC&pg=PA124&lpg=PA124&dq=Il+y+avait+la+Flandre+soubs+la+couronne,+relevant+du+roi+de+France+;+la+Flandre+soubs+l'empire,+relevant+de+l'empire;+et+la+Flandre+allodiale,+relevant+directement+du+comte+de+Flandre.%22*+%7C+Voisin,+pp.+49,+50&source=bl&ots=bnSiI8YwVo&sig=ACfU3U0G6GM0SDkSJ51Ac9Nt4N-rCIRgag&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjD8K_Pu_roAhWVGc0KHdo0D20Q6AEwAHoECAgQAQ#v=onepage&q=Allodiale&f=false|title=The History of the Life and Times of Edward III|date=1869|publisher=Longmans & Green|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=124|language=en}}</ref>\n\nFrom 1051, the House of Flanders also reigned over the County of Hainaut, with [[Baldwin VI, Count of Flanders|Baldwin I of Hainaut]]. In  1119, on the death of [[Baldwin VII, Count of Flanders|Baldwin VII]], the House of Flanders had a series of setbacks but in 1191, the House of Flanders recovered the title of Count of Flanders with [[Baldwin VIII, Count of Flanders|Baldwin VIII]] (Baldwin V of Hainaut). The dynasty established the [[Latin Empire of Constantinople]] during the [[Fourth Crusade]]. It also ruled briefly the County of Namur (1188-1212). The House of Flanders was inherited in 1280 by the descendants of [[Margaret II, Countess of Flanders|Margaret II]].<ref>{{Cite book|last=Jackson|first=Guida M.|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=x3BzmTdQLioC&pg=PA254&lpg=PA254&dq=count+of+flanders+female+succession&source=bl&ots=U6kWpvpuUg&sig=ACfU3U0rTREk137tCuis4P15IcCzcmEImw&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwinvMeZ2_roAhVZZc0KHY7MBbEQ6AEwBHoECAQQAQ#v=onepage&q=count%20of%20flanders%20female%20succession&f=false|title=Women Rulers Throughout the Ages: An Illustrated Guide|last2=Jackson-Laufer|first2=Guida Myrl|last3=Jackson|first3=Lecturer in English Foundations Department Guida M.|date=1999|publisher=ABC-CLIO|isbn=978-1-57607-091-8|language=en}}</ref>\n\nA cadet branch, the House of Boulogne, ruled over the [[County of Boulogne]]. Members of this house joined the [[First Crusade]], established the [[Kingdom of Jerusalem]], and produced its first kings.\n\n== Genealogy ==\n{{Tree list}}\n*[[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin I, Count of Flanders|Baldwin I Iron Arm]], [[Count of Flanders]] (\u2020 879)\n** {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin II, Count of Flanders|Baldwin II the Bald]], Count of Flanders (\u2020 918)\n***[[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Arnulf I, Count of Flanders|Arnulf I the Great]], Count of Flanders (\u2020 965)\n**** Elftrude, born circa 932, married in 964 to [[File:Blason_ville_fr_Guines_(PDC).png|15px]] Siegfried, Count of Gu\u00eenes (\u2020 965)\n**** Hildegarde (934 \u2020 990), married in 943 to [[File:Counts of Holland Arms.svg|15px]] [[Dirk II, Count of Holland]] (930 \u2020 988)\n**** Egbert (937 \u2020 953)\n**** Liutgarde (938 \u2020 964), married in 950 to Wichmann IV, Count of Hamaland and Ghent.\n**** {{Tree list/final branch}}  [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin III, Count of Flanders|Baldwin III]], Count of Flanders (\u2020 962)\n***** {{Tree list/final branch}}  [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Arnulf II, Count of Flanders|Arnulf II]], Count of Flanders (\u2020 988)\n****** Mathilda (\u2020 995 or before)\n****** {{Tree list/final branch}}  [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin IV, Count of Flanders|Baldwin IV the Bearded]] (v.980 \u2020 1035), Count of Flanders (\u2020 1035)\n******* [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin V, Count of Flanders|Baldwin V ''of Lille'']], Count of Flanders (\u2020 1067)\n******** [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[File:Blason fr Hainaut ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin VI, Count of Flanders|Baldwin VI the Good]], (1030 - 1070), Count of Flanders and of Hainaut\n********* [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[File:Blason fr Hainaut ancien.svg|15px]] [[Arnulf III, Count of Flanders|Arnulf III of Flanders]] (1055 \u2020 1071), Count of Flanders and Hainaut\n*********  {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason fr Hainaut ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin II, Count of Hainaut|Baldwin II of Hainaut]] (1056 \u2020 1098), Count of Hainaut\n**********  {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason fr Hainaut ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin III, Count of Hainaut|Baldwin III of Hainaut]] (1088 \u2020 1120), Count of Hainaut\n***********  {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason fr Hainaut ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin IV, Count of Hainaut|Baldwin IV the Builder]] (1108 \u2020 1171), Count of Hainaut\n************ Agnes of Hainaut, married [[File:Blason_Coucy-le-Chateau.svg|15px]] [[Ralph I, Lord of Coucy]]\n************  {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason fr Hainaut ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin V, Count of Hainaut|Baldwin V of Hainaut]] (1150 \u2020 1195), Count of Hainaut\n************* [[Isabella of Hainault]] (\u00b01170- \u20201190), married [[File:Blason pays fr FranceAncien.svg|15px]] [[Philip II of France]] \n************* [[File:Blason Empire Latin de Constantinople.svg|15px]] [[File:Blason comte-des-Flandres.svg|15px]] [[File:Blason fr Hainaut ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin I of Constantinople|Baldwin VI of Hainaut]] (\u00b01171- \u20201205), Count of Flanders and Hainaut, Latin Emperor of Constantinople\n************** [[File:Blason comte-des-Flandres.svg|15px]] [[File:Blason fr Hainaut ancien.svg|15px]] [[Joan, Countess of Flanders|Joan]] (1199-1200 \u2020 1244), Countess  of Flanders and of Hainaut\n**************  {{Tree list/final branch}}  [[File:Blason comte-des-Flandres.svg|15px]] [[File:Blason fr Hainaut ancien.svg|15px]] [[Margaret II, Countess of Flanders|Margaret II]] (ca.1202 \u2020 1280), Countess  of Flanders and of Hainaut\n************* [[Yolanda of Flanders|Yolanda]] (\u00b01175- \u20201219), married [[File:Blason Empire Latin de Constantinople.svg|15px]] [[Peter II of Courtenay]], Latin Emperor of Constantinople\n************* [[File:Namur Arms.svg|15px]] [[Philip I of Namur|Philip the Noble]], Marquis of Namur (\u00b01175- \u20201212) \n************* [[File:Blason Empire Latin de Constantinople.svg|15px]] [[Henry of Flanders|Henry]] (\u00b01176- \u20201216), Latin Emperor of Constantinople\n************* Sybille (\u00b01179- \u20201217), married to [[File:Blason_ville_fr_Beaujeu_(Rh%C3%B4ne).svg|15px]] Guichard IV, Sire of Beaujeu\n*************  {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Fessaloniki.png|15px]] [[Eustace of Flanders|Eustace]] (\u20201217), regent of the [[Kingdom of Thessalonica]]\n******** [[Matilda of Flanders|Matilda]] (1032 - 1083), married in 1053 to [[File:Blason duche fr Normandie.svg|15px]] [[William the Conqueror]]\n********  {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Robert I, Count of Flanders|Robert the Frisian]], (1033 - 1093), Count of Flanders from 1071 to 1093\n********* [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Robert II, Count of Flanders|Robert II]], Count of Flanders from 1093 to 1111\n********** [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin VII, Count of Flanders|Baldwin VII]] (1093-1119), Count of Flanders\n********** Guillaume (1094-1109)\n********** {{Tree list/final branch}}  Philip (1095-) (died young)\n********* [[Adela of Flanders]] (\u2020 1115), married firstly [[File:Ancien blason Danemark.svg|15px]] [[Canute IV of Denmark]]. Married secondly [[File:Coat of Arms of Robert Guiscard.svg|15px]] [[Roger Borsa]], Duke of Apulia.\n**********  {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason Flandre ancien.svg|15px]] [[Charles I, Count of Flanders]] (1084 \u2013 1127)\n********* [[Gertrude of Flanders, Duchess of Lorraine|Gertrude]] (1080 - \u2020 1117), married to [[Henry III, Count of Louvain|Henry III]] (\u2020 1095) Count of Louvain and Brussels, then in 1096 to [[Theodoric II, Duke of Lorraine]] (\u2020 1115).\n********* Philip of Loo, whose illegitimate son [[William of Ypres]] was a claimant to the county of Flanders.\n*********  {{Tree list/final branch}} Ogive, abbess of [[Mesen]].\n******* {{Tree list/final branch}}  [[Judith of Flanders, Countess of Northumbria]] (1037 \u2020 1094), married in 1058 to [[Tostig Godwinson]] (\u2020 1066), [[Earl of Northumbria]], then in 1071 to [[Welf I, Duke of Bavaria]] (\u2020 1101)\n*** {{Tree list/final branch}}  [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Adelolf, Count of Boulogne|Adelolf]] (\u2020 933), [[Count of Boulogne]] \n**** {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Arnulf II, Count of Boulogne|Arnulf II]] (\u2020 971), Count of Boulogne\n*****{{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Arnulf III, Count of Boulogne|Arnulf III]] (\u2020 990), Count of Boulogne\n******[[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin II, Count of Boulogne|Baldwin II]] (\u2020 1025), Count of Boulogne \n*******{{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Eustace I, Count of Boulogne|Eustace I]] (v. 995 \u2020 1049), Count of Boulogne\n******** [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Eustace II, Count of Boulogne|Eustace II]] (\u2020 1087), Count of Boulogne\n********* [[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|15px]] [[Eustace III, Count of Boulogne]] (1056 \u2020 1125)\n********** [[Matilda I, Countess of Boulogne]] (1105 \u2020 1152), married in 1125 to [[Stephen of England]]\n********* [[Godfrey of Bouillon]] (1058 \u2020 1099), [[Duke of Lower Lorraine]], a leader of the [[First Crusade]] and \"Advocate of the Holy Sepulchre\"\n********* {{Tree list/final branch}} [[File:Armoiries de J\u00e9rusalem.svg|15px]] [[Baldwin I of Jerusalem]] (1065 \u2020 1118), accompanied his brother to the Holy Land, became Count of Edessa and then King of Jerusalem\n******** Godfrey (\u2020 1095), Bishop of Paris\n******** [[Lambert II, Count of Lens]] (\u2020 1054)\n******** {{Tree list/final branch}} Gerberge (\u2020 1049), married [[Frederick, Duke of Lower Lorraine]] (1003 \u2020 1065)\n******{{Tree list/final branch}} Arnulf IV, Count of Ternois\n{{Tree list/end}}\n\n==Arms==\n{{Multiple image\n<!-- Essential parameters -->\n | align             = center\n | direction         = <!-- horizontal (default), vertical -->\n | background color  = <!-- box background -->\n\n<!-- Header -->\n | header_background = \n | header_align      = <!-- center (default), left, right -->\n | header            = Arms of the House of Flanders\n\n<!-- Images -->\n | width             = 140\n<!--image 1-->\n | image1            = Blason Flandre ancien.svg\n | caption1          = Count of Flanders (attributed)\n<!--image 2-->\n | image2            = Blason Nord-Pas-De-Calais.svg\n | caption2          = Count of Flanders\n<!--image 3-->\n | image3            = Blason fr Hainaut ancien.svg\n | caption3          = Count of Hainaut (Ancient)\n<!--image 4-->\n | image4            = Blason Empire Latin de Constantinople.svg\n | caption4          = Latin Emperor of Constantinople\n\n<!-- and so on, to a maximum of 10 images (image10) -->\n\n}}\n\n{{Multiple image\n<!-- Essential parameters -->\n | align            