{"title_page": "Khandaani Shafakhana", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2019}}{{Short description|2019 Indian Hindi-language comedy-drama film}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Khandaani Shafakhana\n| image          = Khandaani Shafakhana.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = Shilpi Dasgupta\n| producer       = {{ubl|[[Bhushan Kumar]]|Mahaveer Jain|Mrighdeep Singh Lamba|[[Divya Khosla Kumar]]|[[Krishan Kumar (actor)|Krishan Kumar]]}}\n| writer         = Gautam Mehra\n| based_on       = \n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Sonakshi Sinha]]|[[Varun Sharma]]|[[Annu Kapoor]]|[[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]]}}\n| music          = {{ubl|'''Songs:'''|[[Tanishk Bagchi]]|[[Rochak Kohli]]|[[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]]|[[Payal Dev]]|'''Score:'''|Abhishek Nailwal}}\n| cinematography = Rishi Punjabi\n| editing        = Dev Rao Jadhav\n| studio         = {{ubl|Sundial Productions|[[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]}}\n| distributor    = [[Panorama Studios]]\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2019|8|2}}\n| runtime        = 136 minutes<ref name=BBFC>{{cite web | url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/khandaani-shafakhana-2019 | title=Khandaani Shafakhana | website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] | accessdate=26 July 2019 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726174859/https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/khandaani-shafakhana-2019 | archive-date=26 July 2019 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = \u20b924 crore<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=5697}}</ref>\n| gross          = {{estimation}} \u20b93.98 crore<ref name=\"boxks\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/khandaani-shafakhana/box-office/#bh-movie-box-office|title=Khandaani Shafakhana Box Office|website=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=4 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620094701/https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/khandaani-shafakhana/box-office/#bh-movie-box-office|archive-date=20 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Khandaani Shafakhana''''' ({{trans|Familial clinic}}) is a 2019 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[comedy-drama]] film directed by debutant director Shilpi Dasgupta, and starring [[Sonakshi Sinha]] and [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]] Genda. The supporting cast includes [[Varun Sharma]] and [[Annu Kapoor]]. [[Principal photography]] began on 25 January 2019, and it was theatrically released in India on 2 August 2019.\nIt was considered as a box office disaster due to its poor commercial performance.<ref>https://www.m.rediff.com/amp/movies/report/box-office-khandaani-shafakhana-flops/20190806</ref><ref>https://www.koimoi.com/box-office/khandaani-shafakhana-box-office-day-3-sonakshi-sinhas-film-is-a-disaster/amp/</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nBabita \"Baby\" Bedi, a middle class Punjabi girl, is working as a medical representative and the only earner in the house. She gets constantly shouted at by her boss and is unhappy with her job. Her uncle, who had lent them money earlier, has his eyes fixed upon Baby's house, which is the only remainder of her dead father.\n\nOne day she inherits her uncle, Mamaji's wealth after he is killed by a man. His will states that Baby is the sole heir of his property and that she has to run a [[fertility clinic]] for six months in order to sell it or else she will lose everything. She will have to face many obstacles of this society that is [[Conservatism|conservative]] towards women.\n\nIn order to deal with her old job, she sends Bhooshit, her brother, in place of her, claiming 6 months' sick leave.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Sonakshi Sinha]] as Babita \"Baby\" Bedi\n* [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]] as Gabru Ghataak\n* [[Varun Sharma]] as Bhooshit Bedi\n* [[Annu Kapoor]] as Tagra\n* Priyansh Jora as Lemon Hero\n* [[Kulbhushan Kharbanda]] as Hakim Tarachand aka Mamaji\n* [[Rajesh Sharma (actor)|Rajesh Sharma]] as Judge Joshav Agarwal\n* [[Nadira Babbar]] as Mrs. Bedi\n* Rajiv Gupta as Chachaji\n* [[Diana Penty]] as Sunita (special appearance in song \"Shehar Ki Ladki\")<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/diana-penty-badshah-to-feature-in-sheher-ki-ladki-remake-in-khandaani-shafaakhana-report/story-DF1tDgprCzVpoKpcf6gQDK.html|title=Diana Penty, Badshah to feature in Sheher Ki Ladki remake in Khandaani Shafaakhana\n|publisher=Hindustan Times|access-date=29 June 2019|date=27 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/diana-penty-to-recreate-raveena-tandon-s-shehar-ki-ladki-in-khandaani-shafakhana-1557224-2019-06-27|title=Diana Penty to recreate Raveena Tandon's Shehar Ki Ladki in Khandaani Shafakhana|publisher=India Today|access-date=29 June 2019|date=27 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629024309/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/diana-penty-to-recreate-raveena-tandon-s-shehar-ki-ladki-in-khandaani-shafakhana-1557224-2019-06-27|archive-date=29 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Suniel Shetty]] (special appearance in song \"Shehar Ki Ladki\")<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wionews.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-raveena-tandon-suniel-shetty-to-star-in-remake-of-their-song-sheher-ki-ladki-231946|title=Khandaani Shafakhana: Raveena Tandon, Suniel Shetty to star in remake of their song 'Sheher Ki Ladki'|website=WION|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190702120219/https://www.wionews.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-raveena-tandon-suniel-shetty-to-star-in-remake-of-their-song-sheher-ki-ladki-231946|archive-date=2 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Raveena Tandon]] (special appearance in song \"Shehar Ki Ladki\")<ref name=\":0\"/>\n\n==Production==\nThe [[principal photography]] of the film began in [[Punjab]] in the end of January 2019.<ref name=\":p1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-first-look-sonakshi-sinha-aims-to-dispel-stigma-associated-with-sex-clinics-6847091.html|title=Khandaani Shafakhana first look: Sonakshi Sinha aims to dispel stigma associated with sex clinics|website=Firstpost|access-date=20 June 2019|date=19 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620060604/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-first-look-sonakshi-sinha-aims-to-dispel-stigma-associated-with-sex-clinics-6847091.html|archive-date=20 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The film also marks the acting debut of Badshah.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/sonakshi-sinha-releases-first-poster-of-badshah-s-debut-film-khandaani-shafakhana-1552136-2019-06-19|title=Sonakshi Sinha releases first poster of Badshah's debut film Khandaani Shafakhana|newspaper=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-06-20|agency=Ist|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620045441/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/sonakshi-sinha-releases-first-poster-of-badshah-s-debut-film-khandaani-shafakhana-1552136-2019-06-19|archive-date=20 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing and release==\nThe first look poster of the film was released by [[Sonakshi Sinha]] on 19 June 2019.<ref name=\":l0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/khandaani-shafakhana-poster-sonakshi-sinha-is-baby-bedi-says-the-more-she-will-talk-the-more-embarrassed-people-will-be/story-QNvpxtlkSIOr2002DRqgqM.html|title=Khandaani Shafakhana poster: Sonakshi Sinha is Baby Bedi, says the more she will talk, the more embarrassed people will be|date=2019-06-19|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2019-06-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620045437/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/khandaani-shafakhana-poster-sonakshi-sinha-is-baby-bedi-says-the-more-she-will-talk-the-more-embarrassed-people-will-be/story-QNvpxtlkSIOr2002DRqgqM.html|archive-date=20 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The next day another poster was unveiled presenting the lead cast of the film in a teaser look.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-sonakshi-sinhas-film-gets-new-poster-trailer-to-release-on-21-june-6853921.html|title=Khandaani Shafakhana: Sonakshi Sinha's film gets new poster; trailer to release on 21 June|website=Firstpost|access-date=20 June 2019|date=20 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620165151/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-sonakshi-sinhas-film-gets-new-poster-trailer-to-release-on-21-june-6853921.html|archive-date=20 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The official trailer of the film was released on 21 June 2019 by [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=-JeXtTqn4yM|title=Official Trailer: Khandaani Shafakhana {{!}} Sonakshi Sinha {{!}} Badshah {{!}} Varun Sharma|publisher=T Series|website=YouTube|date=21 June 2019|access-date=21 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190621232307/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-JeXtTqn4yM|archive-date=21 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe film slated to release on 2 August 2019, after the initial release dates were changed.<ref name=\":l1\">{{Cite web|url=https://zeenews.india.com/bollywood/sonakshi-sinha-starrer-khandaani-shafakhana-gets-a-new-release-date-2214726.html|title=Sonakshi Sinha starrer `Khandaani Shafakhana` gets a new release date|website=Zee News|access-date=27 June 2019|date=27 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190627071450/https://zeenews.india.com/bollywood/sonakshi-sinha-starrer-khandaani-shafakhana-gets-a-new-release-date-2214726.html|archive-date=27 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The film certified with a runtime of 136 minutes by [[British Board of Film Classification]], was released on 2 August 2019.<ref name=BBFC />\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Khandaani Shafakhana\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Tanishk Bagchi]], [[Rochak Kohli]], [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]] and [[Payal Dev]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 26 July 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiosaavn.com/album/khandaani-shafakhana/b3a3KSGTDE8|title=Khandaani Shafakhana - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack|publisher=Jio Saavn|access-date=26 July 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726162801/https://www.jiosaavn.com/album/khandaani-shafakhana/b3a3KSGTDE8|archive-date=26 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| recorded   = 2019\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 21:57\n| language   = [[Hindi]]\n| label      = [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n| producer   =\n| misc       =  {{External media\n | audio1     = {{YouTube|QzRgqdVZf3M|Official Audio Jukebox}}\n}}}}\nThe music of the film is composed by [[Tanishk Bagchi]], [[Rochak Kohli]], [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]] and [[Payal Dev]] and lyrics written by Badshah, Tanishk Bagchi, [[Kumaar]], Mellow D, [[Shabbir Ahmed (lyricist)|Shabbir Ahmed]] Gautam G Sharma and Gurpreet Saini.\nThe song \"Shehar Ki Ladki\" which is picturised on [[Diana Penty]], is a recreated song from [[Rakshak]] (1996), originally pictured on Raveena Tandon<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/raveena-tandons-song-sheher-ki-ladki-to-be-recreated-for-khandaani-shafakhana-2060380|title=Raveena Tandon's Song Sheher Ki Ladki To Be Recreated For Khandaani Shafakhana|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2019-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190701091325/https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/raveena-tandons-song-sheher-ki-ladki-to-be-recreated-for-khandaani-shafakhana-2060380|archive-date=1 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> It was revealed that the original cast of [[Raveena Tandon]] and [[Suniel Shetty]] that featured in song sequence will appear in this song sequence to create nostalgic moments. The song was originally sung by [[Abhijeet Bhattacharya]] and [[Chandana Dixit]] and composed by [[Anand-Milind]] in 1996.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/raveena-tandon-suniel-shetty-to-make-an-appearance-in-diana-penty-s-sheher-ki-ladki-remake-for-khandaani-shafakhana/story-5LNp367n0ucsryuO4CsXYJ.html|title=Raveena Tandon, Suniel Shetty to make an appearance in Diana Penty's Sheher Ki Ladki remake for Khandaani Shafakhana|date=2019-06-30|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190702120637/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/raveena-tandon-suniel-shetty-to-make-an-appearance-in-diana-penty-s-sheher-ki-ladki-remake-for-khandaani-shafakhana/story-5LNp367n0ucsryuO4CsXYJ.html|archive-date=2 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n{{Tracklist\n| headline=Track listing\n| total_length= 21:57\n| extra_column=Singer(s)\n| title1= Koka\n| extra1= [[Jasbir Jassi]], [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]], [[Dhvani Bhanushali]]\n| music1 = [[Tanishk Bagchi]]\n| lyrics1 = Tanishk Bagchi, Mellow D\n| length1= 2:56\n| title2 = Shehar Ki Ladki \n| extra2 = Badshah, [[Tulsi Kumar]], Abhijeet, Chandra Dixit\n| music2 = [[Anand Milind]], Tanishk Bagchi\n| lyrics2 =Deepak Chaudhary, Tanishk Bagchi\n| length2 = 2:52\n| title3 = Dil Jaaniye\n| extra3 = [[Jubin Nautiyal]], [[Tulsi Kumar]]\n| music3 = [[Payal Dev]]\n| lyrics3 = [[Shabbir Ahmed (lyricist)|Shabbir Ahmed]]\n| length3 = 4:42\n| title4 = Saans To Le Le\n| extra4 = Badshah, Rico\n| music4 = Badshah\n| lyrics4 = Badshah\n| length4 = 3:17\n| title5 = Udd Jaa\n| extra5 = [[Tochi Raina]]\n| music5 = [[Rochak Kohli]]\n| lyrics5 = [[Kumaar]]\n| length5 = 4:11\n| title6 = Bheege Mann\n| extra6 = Altamash Faridi\n| music6 = Rochak Kohli\n| lyrics6 = Gautam G Sharma, Gurpreet Saini\n| length6 = 3:59\n}}\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Critical reception ===\nRaja Sen of The ''[[Hindustan Times]]'' wrote, \"As a nation, we need to talk about sex. We're obviously having enough of it to not be scandalised this easy. It's not all shock and haww\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/khandaani-shafakhana-movie-review-in-case-you-d-forgotten-sonakshi-sinha-is-no-ayushmann-khurrana/story-87BZ8tAq15G6JlkWYwDvuO.html|title=Khandaani Shafakhana movie review: In case you'd forgotten, Sonakshi Sinha is no Ayushmann Khurrana|date=2019-08-02|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2019-08-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190802145042/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/khandaani-shafakhana-movie-review-in-case-you-d-forgotten-sonakshi-sinha-is-no-ayushmann-khurrana/story-87BZ8tAq15G6JlkWYwDvuO.html|archive-date=2 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>[[Namrata Joshi]] of ''[[The Hindu]]'' wrote, \"Khandaani Shafakhana may have a laudable message at its core, but gets bogged down by its own overly righteous attempt to 'educate' \u2013 that sex is not gandi baat, ashleel aur aapattijanak (bad thing, obscene and unacceptable), nothing to be shameful about.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/khandaani-shafakhana-review/article28795649.ece|title='Khandaani Shafakhana' review: We don't need no sex education|last=Joshi|first=Namrata|date=2019-08-02|work=The Hindu|access-date=2019-08-02|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> Ronak Kotecha of ''[[The Times of India]]'' wrote, \"In the past, we have seen films like 'Vicky Donor' and 'Shubh Mangal Savadhan' handle sensitive subjects (read sperm donation and erectile dysfunction) with class, tact and comedy. While this film's intent is bang on, what it really needed was a heavier dose of humour and entertainment\".<ref>{{Citation|title=Khandaani Shafakhana Review {3/5}: While the intent is bang on, the film is not all that funny|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/khandaani-shafakhana/movie-review/70485155.cms|access-date=2019-08-02}}</ref> Umesh Punwani of ''[[Koimoi]]'' wrote, \"All said and done, the intent is pure but the story isn't pious. This could've been another Shubh Mangal Saavdhan, only if it had better writing. Skip it to watch it on a lazy day months from now, still not sure if you'll be able to finish it\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.koimoi.com/reviews/khandaani-shafakhana-movie-review-pure-intent-with-a-not-so-pious-story/|title=Khandaani Shafakhana Movie Review Out - Stars Sonakshi Sinha, Badshah & More!|last=Punwani|first=Umesh|date=2019-08-02|website=Koimoi|language=en-US|access-date=2019-08-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190802120900/https://www.koimoi.com/reviews/khandaani-shafakhana-movie-review-pure-intent-with-a-not-so-pious-story/|archive-date=2 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn review aggregator website Imdb, the movie scored an average rating of 4.9/10<ref>https://m.imdb.com/title/tt10519182/</ref>\n\n===Box office===\n''Khandaani Shafakhana'' had the opening day collection of {{INR}}75 lacs and the second day collection of {{INR}}80 lacs, whereas the third day collection was {{INR}}1.20 crore, taking its total opening weekend collection to {{INR}}2.75 crore.<ref name=\"boxks\"/>\n\n{{As of|2019|08|3}}, with a gross of {{INR}}3.27 crore in India and {{INR}}0.71 crore overseas, the film has a worldwide gross collection of {{INR}}3.98 crore.<ref name=\"boxks\"/>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links == \n*{{IMDB title|tt10519182}}\n*[https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/khandaani-shafakhana/  ''Khandaani Shafakhana''] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/khandaani_shafakhana}}\n\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Punjab, India]]\n[[Category:Films featuring an item number]]\n[[Category:T-Series films]]\n[[Category:2019 directorial debut films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=June 2019}}{{Short description|2019 Indian Hindi-language comedy-drama film}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Khandaani Shafakhana\n| image          = Khandaani Shafakhana.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = Shilpi Dasgupta\n| producer       = {{ubl|[[Bhushan Kumar]]|Mahaveer Jain|Mrighdeep Singh Lamba|[[Divya Khosla Kumar]]|[[Krishan Kumar (actor)|Krishan Kumar]]}}\n| writer         = Gautam Mehra\n| based_on       = \n| starring       = {{ubl|[[Sonakshi Sinha]]|[[Varun Sharma]]|[[Annu Kapoor]]|[[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]]}}\n| music          = {{ubl|'''Songs:'''|[[Tanishk Bagchi]]|[[Rochak Kohli]]|[[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]]|[[Payal Dev]]|'''Score:'''|Abhishek Nailwal}}\n| cinematography = Rishi Punjabi\n| editing        = Dev Rao Jadhav\n| studio         = {{ubl|Sundial Productions|[[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]}}\n| distributor    = [[Panorama Studios]]\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2019|8|2}}\n| runtime        = 136 minutes<ref name=BBFC>{{cite web | url=https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/khandaani-shafakhana-2019 | title=Khandaani Shafakhana | website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] | accessdate=26 July 2019 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190726174859/https://bbfc.co.uk/releases/khandaani-shafakhana-2019 | archive-date=26 July 2019 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| budget         = \u20b924 crore<ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficeindia.com/movie.php?movieid=5697}}</ref>\n| gross          = {{estimation}} \u20b93.98 crore<ref name=\"boxks\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/khandaani-shafakhana/box-office/#bh-movie-box-office|title=Khandaani Shafakhana Box Office|website=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=4 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620094701/https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/khandaani-shafakhana/box-office/#bh-movie-box-office|archive-date=20 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Khandaani Shafakhana''''' ({{trans|Familial clinic}}) is a 2019 Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[comedy-drama]] film directed by debutant director Shilpi Dasgupta, and starring [[Sonakshi Sinha]] and [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]]. The supporting cast includes [[Varun Sharma]] and [[Annu Kapoor]]. [[Principal photography]] began on 25 January 2019, and it was theatrically released in India on 2 August 2019.\nIt was considered as a box office disaster due to its poor commercial performance.<ref>https://www.m.rediff.com/amp/movies/report/box-office-khandaani-shafakhana-flops/20190806</ref><ref>https://www.koimoi.com/box-office/khandaani-shafakhana-box-office-day-3-sonakshi-sinhas-film-is-a-disaster/amp/</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nBabita \"Baby\" Bedi, a middle class Punjabi girl, is working as a medical representative and the only earner in the house. She gets constantly shouted at by her boss and is unhappy with her job. Her uncle, who had lent them money earlier, has his eyes fixed upon Baby's house, which is the only remainder of her dead father.\n\nOne day she inherits her uncle, Mamaji's wealth after he is killed by a man. His will states that Baby is the sole heir of his property and that she has to run a [[fertility clinic]] for six months in order to sell it or else she will lose everything. She will have to face many obstacles of this society that is [[Conservatism|conservative]] towards women.\n\nIn order to deal with her old job, she sends Bhooshit, her brother, in place of her, claiming 6 months' sick leave.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Sonakshi Sinha]] as Babita \"Baby\" Bedi\n* [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]] as Gabru Ghataak\n* [[Varun Sharma]] as Bhooshit Bedi\n* [[Annu Kapoor]] as Tagra\n* Priyansh Jora as Lemon Hero\n* [[Kulbhushan Kharbanda]] as Hakim Tarachand aka Mamaji\n* [[Rajesh Sharma (actor)|Rajesh Sharma]] as Judge Joshav Agarwal\n* [[Nadira Babbar]] as Mrs. Bedi\n* Rajiv Gupta as Chachaji\n* [[Diana Penty]] as Sunita (special appearance in song \"Shehar Ki Ladki\")<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/diana-penty-badshah-to-feature-in-sheher-ki-ladki-remake-in-khandaani-shafaakhana-report/story-DF1tDgprCzVpoKpcf6gQDK.html|title=Diana Penty, Badshah to feature in Sheher Ki Ladki remake in Khandaani Shafaakhana\n|publisher=Hindustan Times|access-date=29 June 2019|date=27 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/diana-penty-to-recreate-raveena-tandon-s-shehar-ki-ladki-in-khandaani-shafakhana-1557224-2019-06-27|title=Diana Penty to recreate Raveena Tandon's Shehar Ki Ladki in Khandaani Shafakhana|publisher=India Today|access-date=29 June 2019|date=27 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190629024309/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/diana-penty-to-recreate-raveena-tandon-s-shehar-ki-ladki-in-khandaani-shafakhana-1557224-2019-06-27|archive-date=29 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Suniel Shetty]] (special appearance in song \"Shehar Ki Ladki\")<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.wionews.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-raveena-tandon-suniel-shetty-to-star-in-remake-of-their-song-sheher-ki-ladki-231946|title=Khandaani Shafakhana: Raveena Tandon, Suniel Shetty to star in remake of their song 'Sheher Ki Ladki'|website=WION|language=en|access-date=2019-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190702120219/https://www.wionews.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-raveena-tandon-suniel-shetty-to-star-in-remake-of-their-song-sheher-ki-ladki-231946|archive-date=2 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*[[Raveena Tandon]] (special appearance in song \"Shehar Ki Ladki\")<ref name=\":0\"/>\n\n==Production==\nThe [[principal photography]] of the film began in [[Punjab]] in the end of January 2019.<ref name=\":p1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-first-look-sonakshi-sinha-aims-to-dispel-stigma-associated-with-sex-clinics-6847091.html|title=Khandaani Shafakhana first look: Sonakshi Sinha aims to dispel stigma associated with sex clinics|website=Firstpost|access-date=20 June 2019|date=19 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620060604/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-first-look-sonakshi-sinha-aims-to-dispel-stigma-associated-with-sex-clinics-6847091.html|archive-date=20 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The film also marks the acting debut of Badshah.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/sonakshi-sinha-releases-first-poster-of-badshah-s-debut-film-khandaani-shafakhana-1552136-2019-06-19|title=Sonakshi Sinha releases first poster of Badshah's debut film Khandaani Shafakhana|newspaper=India Today|language=en|access-date=2019-06-20|agency=Ist|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620045441/https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/bollywood/story/sonakshi-sinha-releases-first-poster-of-badshah-s-debut-film-khandaani-shafakhana-1552136-2019-06-19|archive-date=20 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Marketing and release==\nThe first look poster of the film was released by [[Sonakshi Sinha]] on 19 June 2019.<ref name=\":l0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/khandaani-shafakhana-poster-sonakshi-sinha-is-baby-bedi-says-the-more-she-will-talk-the-more-embarrassed-people-will-be/story-QNvpxtlkSIOr2002DRqgqM.html|title=Khandaani Shafakhana poster: Sonakshi Sinha is Baby Bedi, says the more she will talk, the more embarrassed people will be|date=2019-06-19|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2019-06-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620045437/https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/khandaani-shafakhana-poster-sonakshi-sinha-is-baby-bedi-says-the-more-she-will-talk-the-more-embarrassed-people-will-be/story-QNvpxtlkSIOr2002DRqgqM.html|archive-date=20 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The next day another poster was unveiled presenting the lead cast of the film in a teaser look.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-sonakshi-sinhas-film-gets-new-poster-trailer-to-release-on-21-june-6853921.html|title=Khandaani Shafakhana: Sonakshi Sinha's film gets new poster; trailer to release on 21 June|website=Firstpost|access-date=20 June 2019|date=20 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190620165151/https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/khandaani-shafakhana-sonakshi-sinhas-film-gets-new-poster-trailer-to-release-on-21-june-6853921.html|archive-date=20 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The official trailer of the film was released on 21 June 2019 by [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=-JeXtTqn4yM|title=Official Trailer: Khandaani Shafakhana {{!}} Sonakshi Sinha {{!}} Badshah {{!}} Varun Sharma|publisher=T Series|website=YouTube|date=21 June 2019|access-date=21 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190621232307/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-JeXtTqn4yM|archive-date=21 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe film slated to release on 2 August 2019, after the initial release dates were changed.<ref name=\":l1\">{{Cite web|url=https://zeenews.india.com/bollywood/sonakshi-sinha-starrer-khandaani-shafakhana-gets-a-new-release-date-2214726.html|title=Sonakshi Sinha starrer `Khandaani Shafakhana` gets a new release date|website=Zee News|access-date=27 June 2019|date=27 June 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190627071450/https://zeenews.india.com/bollywood/sonakshi-sinha-starrer-khandaani-shafakhana-gets-a-new-release-date-2214726.html|archive-date=27 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The film certified with a runtime of 136 minutes by [[British Board of Film Classification]], was released on 2 August 2019.<ref name=BBFC />\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Khandaani Shafakhana\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Tanishk Bagchi]], [[Rochak Kohli]], [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]] and [[Payal Dev]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = 26 July 2019<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jiosaavn.com/album/khandaani-shafakhana/b3a3KSGTDE8|title=Khandaani Shafakhana - Original Motion Picture Soundtrack|publisher=Jio Saavn|access-date=26 July 2019|archive-u